{#
  Escalate prompt — hand off cleanly to a human tier-2 agent.

  Context variables:
    customer_question: string
    conversation_summary: string  — what the agent has tried so far
    customer:    { id, name, plan, status }
    handoff_queue: string         — destination queue id
    sentiment:   { score, label } — score in [-1, 1]
#}
The customer asked:

  "{{ customer_question }}"

What we have tried so far:
{{ conversation_summary }}

Customer:
  id:     {{ customer.id }}
  plan:   {{ customer.plan }}
  status: {{ customer.status }}
Sentiment: {{ sentiment.label }} ({{ sentiment.score }})

You have decided to escalate. Do the following, in order:

1. Call `ticket.create` with:
     - priority chosen by sentiment (high if sentiment.score < -0.3, else
       normal)
     - tags: ["escalation", "{{ customer.plan }}"]
     - summary: <= 240 chars, written for a human agent, not the customer
2. Call `ticket.escalate` routing to `{{ handoff_queue }}`.
3. Reply to the customer in <= 3 sentences:
     - Acknowledge the issue in their words.
     - State that a specialist has been engaged.
     - Give them the ticket id and an expected first-response window.

Do not promise a resolution outcome. Do not invent SLAs.
